# Walkthrough: JEEify "Same to Same" Website Implementation

I have successfully built the JEEify platform according to the "Slate & Ember" design system. The implementation uses **Next.js**, **Vanilla CSS**, and **TypeScript** to achieve a premium, high-fidelity experience.

## Key Accomplishments

### 1. Slate & Ember Design System
- **Palette**: Deep Navy (#0F172A), Slate Secondary (#505F76), and Bright Orange CTA (#F97316).
- **Typography**: Dual-font system with `Plus Jakarta Sans` for headlines and `Inter` for technical data.
- **Atmospheric Depth**: Implemented tonally layered backgrounds and frosted glass navigation for a modern "Academic Architect" aesthetic.

### 2. High-Fidelity Screens
- **Landing Page**: Implemented the hero section with the "Architectural Precision" tagline and active mock test cards with status badges.
- **Aspirant Analytics**: Built a data-dense dashboard with score trends, accuracy circular progress, and a topic-wise effort heatmap.
- **Video Library**: Created a streaming-style library with featured masterclasses and categorized subject sections.
- **NTA-Style Test Engine**: Replicated the official JEE mock test interface, including the question palette, timer, and NTA-specific navigation buttons.

## Visual Overview

![JEEify Platform Overview](/Users/raviranjankumargupta/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6fb532d2-c2ba-4bfb-914d-cee924ef1cd0/jeeify_platform_overview_1774267370078.png)

## Technical Summary
- **Framework**: Next.js (Page Router)
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS with CSS Modules and `styled-jsx` for component-level precision.
- **Icons**: Lucide-React for technical and crisp iconography.
- **Components**: Reusable UI primitives (Buttons, Cards, Badges) built from the design system tokens.

## How to Run
```bash
# Navigate to the project directory
cd /Users/raviranjankumargupta/JEEify

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start the development server
npm run dev
```
Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser to see the result.
